cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, specifically on interpreting word embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of an RNN, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms to generate textual definitions, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of context and semantic meaning, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of high-dimensional sparse vectors, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
